translated: Järemo, Uno Gösta, city treasurer, Eksjö, b. 11/12/96 in Ljungarum, Jönköping. Married once to Sigrid Gullers in 1926, with whom he had five children: Inga-Stina b. 1927, Ann-Mari b. 1929, Johan b. 1934, Gunnar b. 1935, and Annika b. 1941. He passed the studentexamen in Jönköping in 1915, the civil engineering exam at CTI in 1919, and the DSI (communications line) in 1931. He went on a study trip to Denmark in 1926. He was employed at Swedish Slate Works from 1919 to 1921, a teacher at various folk high schools from 1921 to 1930, city treasurer in Hässelby Villastad from 1931 to 1937, and city treasurer in Eksjö from 1937 onwards. He was appointed Royal Treasurer in Eksjö's city eastern tax district from 1939 and was in charge of the funds for the Swedish Red Cross Seaside Resort Hamnaryd from 1944. He was also a committee member of the HSB in Eksjö from 1945.
